ng child IDs, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a success. Do not mix implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260512T230927-c39ab0e9/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;`.ddx/executions/20260512T230927-c39ab0e9/no_changes_rationale.txt` must contain one:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` reject.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;To request orchestrator decomposition, add `orchestrator_action: decompose` alongside `status: open`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260512T230927-c39ab0e9/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260512T230927-c39ab0e9/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and project defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-70a432b5\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003eStory 16.3: Specs + cross-cutting e2e + raw-transcript-viewed audit event\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;FEAT-008, FEAT-010, and FEAT-019 specs are missing the documentation sections required to make the Story-16 run-detail page and its evidence browser official. Without spec updates, the run-detail page, trust boundary statement, and raw-transcript audit event are undocumented platform behaviors.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE\u0026#xA;- docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-008-*.md: missing a Run-detail-page subsection describing the trust boundary (\u0026#39;Anyone with project read access sees raw prompts, responses, stderr, tool args\u0026#39;) and evidence browser whitelist (allowed extensions + 64KB cap).\u0026#xA;- docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-010-*.md: Run resolver contract does not include prompt, response, stderr, toolCalls(first, after), bundleFiles[], bundleFile(path) with bundle-root confinement, or normalized ToolCallEntry.\u0026#xA;- docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-019-*.md: review surface does not point to /runs/[runId] deep page.\u0026#xA;- No \u0026#39;raw transcript viewed\u0026#39; audit event exists in the server or schema.\u0026#xA;- Depends on ddx-f04faa86 (16.1 page) and ddx-4cd64068 (16.2 evidence tab).\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;- Update FEAT-008: add Run-detail-page subsection with trust-boundary statement + evidence whitelist (*.txt, *.md, manifest.json, prompt.md, result.json, files \u0026lt; 64KB; no Markdown rendering in evidence tab).\u0026#xA;- Update FEAT-010: extend Run resolver contract with prompt, response, stderr, toolCalls(first, after), bundleFiles[], bundleFile(path) with bundle-root confinement; document normalized ToolCallEntry as canonical store populated at drain.\u0026#xA;- Update FEAT-019: review surface section updated to link to /runs/[runId] deep page.\u0026#xA;- Add \u0026#39;raw transcript viewed\u0026#39; audit event in server (emitted on prompt/response/transcript access).\u0026#xA;- Add cross-cutting e2e: full prompt/response/tool-trace/evidence-list end-to-end via Playwright.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;- Frontend implementation (that is Story 16.1 and 16.2).\u0026#xA;- New auth or role-based access control beyond what the trust boundary statement documents.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. FEAT-008 spec updated with Run-detail-page subsection + trust-boundary statement + evidence whitelist.\u0026#xA;2. FEAT-010 spec updated with extended Run resolver contract + drain-time persistence note + ToolCallEntry definition.\u0026#xA;3. FEAT-019 spec updated with link from review surface to /runs/[runId].\u0026#xA;4. \u0026#39;raw transcript viewed\u0026#39; audit event emitted on access and covered by test (TestAuditEvent_RawTranscriptViewed).\u0026#xA;5. Cross-cutting e2e test exercises full prompt visible + response visible + tool trace visible + evidence list visible: test(\u0026#39;full stack: prompt/response/tool-trace/evidence\u0026#39;, ...) Playwright test.\u0026#xA;6. p95 dataset (200 tool calls, 30 evidence files) all tabs render and become interactive within one render frame.\u0026#xA;7. bun run test:e2e green.\u0026#xA;8. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:2, story:16, ac-quality:needs-refinement\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-a8a18cb7\" base-rev=\"32c9cd79b50f1003ad9e7b90ccf1c7acec5d308b\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260512T230927-c39ab0e9\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cnote\u003eNo governing references were pre-resolved. The bead description above is the primary contract. If it names files, specs, or prior beads, read those before editing. Ground decisions in what is already in the repository; do not guess.\u003c/note\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","attempt_id":"20260512T230927-c39ab0e9","base_rev":"32c9cd79b50f1003ad9e7b90ccf1c7acec5d308b","bead_id":"ddx-70a432b5","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260512T230927-c39ab0e9","correlation_id":"ddx-70a432b5:20260512T230927-c39ab0e9","prompt_file"